Introduction

Tsuki is a Japanese dancer, singer, and model signed under MYSTIC Story. She joined the company in 2019 and participated in the third season of the Japanese survival show "Popteen Cover Girl War" alongside fellow member Siyoon, which led to her becoming a regular model for the magazine starting in November 2019.

On November 25, 2020, Tsuki, using the stage name TARU, debuted as a member of the subunit MAGICOUR from the Japanese girl group 7+ME LINK with the single "MAGIC". She graduated from the group in December 2020.

She was officially introduced as part of Mystic Rookies on February 19, 2020, and later became a member of Billlie, debuting with the group on November 10, 2021, through the mini album "The Billage of Perception : Chapter One".

Tsuki began her role as an MC on MBC's "Show Champion" on February 8, 2023, alongside Moon Sua and WOOAH's Nana, with her final broadcast on November 15, 2023.

On March 24, 2023, it was announced that Tsuki would host the Japanese K-pop radio show "Tsuki ENT.VIEW," which began airing on April 8, 2023.

In 2023, Tsuki participated in the Netflix semi-reality show "Zombieverse," which premiered on August 8, 2023. She also appeared in its second season, "Zombieverse: New Blood," which aired on November 19, 2024.
